<article>
    <h1>KARYN LIM, IN&#xAD;DUS&#xAD;TRIAL DE&#xAD;SIGNER</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201024/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-10-24"><time>2020-10-24</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE HOME AND GARDEN</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Min­i­mal­ist aes­thet­ics that al­low a prod­uct’s con­cept to shine through char­ac­terise the work of Karyn Lim, 28, who col­lab­o­rates with brands to con­cep­tu­alise and de­velop prod­ucts and ac­ces­sories.</p>
    <p>Her love of con­tem­po­rary de­sign started dur­ing an ex­change pro­gramme in Paris.</p>
    <p>Since then, she has show­cased her works at Mi­lan De­sign Week and de­signed for brands like fur­nish­ings la­bel Zan­otta and tech gi­ant Sam­sung, as well as worked along­side prom­i­nent de­sign­ers New Zealand­born Sabine Marcelis and French­man Er­wan Bouroul­lec.</p>
    <p>The re­cent grad­u­ate of Switzer­land’s Lau­sanne Univer­sity of Art and De­sign, where she has been study­ing lux­ury de­sign and crafts­man­ship, is look­ing for­ward to work­ing with lo­cal and in­ter­na­tional brands, man­u­fac­tur­ers and ar­ti­sans.</p>
    <p>Info: Go to www.karyn­lim.com or @karyn.lim on In­sta­gram</p>

